The paper discusses the forensic analysis of mobile health applications, which involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR) and data collection (cs.DC). The privacy concerns associated with the use of such apps also fall under the category of cybercrime (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the user experience and interface design of the apps, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper proposes a taxonomy for the artefacts of forensic interest, which could be considered as a form of information retrieval (cs.SI).
